  "text": "Purpose specification and inference approaches rely on static code analysis of apps [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] or contextaware and network traffic analysis [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Some tools rely on taxonomies to specify and infer categories of purposes. TaintDroid [CITATION_7] categorized purposes into legitimate or non-legitimate. Others have adopted more complicated taxonomies with hierarchies of purpose categories [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . Data Controller Indicators [CITATION_12] distinguished among core functionality, non-core functionality, and marketing.",
